-- Czech Republic Plans $2 Billion Dollar Bonds, Ex-Minister Janota Tells MFD
-- Krystof Chamonikolas
-- 2010-07-15T08:03:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/czech-republic-plans-2-billion-dollar-bonds-ex-minister-janota-tells-mfd.html

          
          
             The Czech government plans to sell
as much as $2 billion of dollar bonds to diversify from koruna
and euro debt,  Eduard Janota , whose term as finance minister
ended this week, said in an interview for Mlada Fronta Dnes
 newspaper .  
